---
import { Activity, BadgeDollarSign, Check, Binoculars } from "@lucide/astro";
import ProblemRotator from "../React/ProblemRotator.tsx";
const tabs = [
  {
    tabTitle: "Beyond looks",
    tabContent:
      "A website that looks great but is not created for the target audience or lacks clear and compelling call to action, will fail to gain qualified leads and conversions. Just having a site with a nice design is not enough; so just using a template that is attractive and replacing the content with yours will not bring in more customers.",
    largerContent:
      "Website design can help you establish a strong brand identity. The layout, graphics, and color schemes can be used to create a consistent look and feel that represents your brand. A strong brand identity can help you stand out from the competition and attract more customers.",
  },
  {
    tabTitle: "Built better",
    tabContent:
      "Many customers use mobile devices to search for local businesses, and not having a mobile-friendly website can lead to missed opportunities. Matter of fact over 60% of businesses found online are by their mobile sites.  We make fast, responsive, mobile-first web design & development that fit your needs.",
    largerContent:
      "The dirty little secret in the web industry is most web sites are slow.  Find the top 5 web designers in your area and put their web address into page speed insights you will find most will fail. And not by a little.  Many sites will only score a 30%. If you wont accept a 30% on your kids math test why accept it on your website?",
  },
  {
    tabTitle: "Getting noticed",
    tabContent:
      "Is your website struggling to get noticed? This often happens when it’s not set up to show up in search results, doesn’t have enough valuable content, or isn’t connected with social media. Showing up on the 8th page of a Google search does not help business will not help you find potential customers.",
    largerContent:
      "If your website has fast load speeds and provides a better user experience, it will likely rank higher in search engine results. Users place a high value  website's content and technical features is crucial.",
  },
  {
    tabTitle: "Tailor made",
    tabContent:
      "If your website isn’t set up properly, it can be hard to attract and keep visitors. It might not feel personal, making it tough to bring in new customers or keep the ones you already have. A confusing or frustrating design can give your competitors an edge. Your site must be made for your customers.",
    largerContent:
      "Are you struggling to turn website visitors into customers? You're not alone. Many businesses fail to convert visitors into leads, sales, or subscribers, and that's where Conversion Rate Optimization (CRO) comes in. By optimizing your website and marketing campaigns, you can increase your conversion rate and drive more revenue.",
  },
];
const problems = [
  {
    id: 1,
    icon: Activity,
    title: "Capital Leaks & Conversions",
    description:
      "A staggering number of government and enterprise websites have a bounce rate over 60%. This isn't just an analytics metric; it's a direct loss of potential contracts, user engagement, and capital. When your interface creates friction, you are effectively paying a tax to your competitors every time a procurement officer Googles a solution.",
    image: "/images/problems/low_engagement.webp",
  },
  {
    id: 2,
    icon: BadgeDollarSign,
    title: "The Invisibility Tax",
    description:
      "You have 'Big Game' logos but a 'Small Game' digital footprint. If your site isn't fully optimized for modern search infrastructure and mobile-first indexing, you are invisible to the very institutions you are trying to reach. A confusing user journey can cause up to a quarter of your high-value pipeline to be abandoned before they ever speak to sales.",
    image: "/images/problems/donations.webp",
  },
  {
    id: 3,
    icon: Check,
    title: "Loss of Institutional Trust",
    description:
      "Your website is your organization's digital storefront. Studies show that 75% of users judge an organization's credibility based on its UI/UX. If your site feels like a budget template, it creates cognitive dissonance for $50k+ contracts. In a competitive space where precision matters, you cannot afford to have your digital presence undermine your authority.",
    image: "/images/problems/credibility.webp",
  },
  {
    id: 4,
    icon: Binoculars,
    title: "Outdated Technical Infrastructure",
    description:
      "Even with high-quality offerings, if your site is built on bloated, legacy frameworks (like traditional WordPress setups), you are sacrificing speed, security, and scalability. Institutional clients require lightning-fast, highly secure platforms. You are being out-maneuvered by organizations deploying modern, high-velocity Astro architectures.",
    image: "/images/problems/seo.webp",
  },
];
---

<section class="bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-950 py-16 lg:py-24" id="leaks">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 md:px-6">
    <div class="flex flex-col mx-auto justify-center">
      <div class="text-center mb-12 lg:mb-20">
        <span
          class="inline-block py-1 px-3 rounded-full bg-teal-50 dark:bg-teal-900/30 text-teal-600 dark:text-teal-400 text-sm font-bold tracking-widest uppercase mb-4"
        >
          Efficiency Audit
        </span>
        <h2
          class="text-3xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl tracking-tight font-extrabold text-slate-900 dark:text-white max-w-4xl mx-auto leading-tight"
        >
          Is Your Digital Infrastructure <span class="text-teal-500"
            >Leaking Capital?</span
          >
        </h2>
      </div>
      <div
        class="h-full w-full bg-white dark:bg-slate-900 p-8 lg:p-12 rounded-3xl shadow-sm border border-slate-100 dark:border-slate-800"
      >
        <ProblemRotator
          primaryColor="teal-500"
          progressGradientDark="bg-gradient-to-r from-teal-400 to-teal-600"
          progressGradientLight="bg-gradient-to-r from-teal-400 to-teal-500"
          problems={problems}
          client:visible
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .custom-tabs {
    grid-template-columns: 200px 1fr;
  }
</style>
